sentences: Bejarano was featured on NBC's The Today Show with Natalie Morales as the “Woman Breaking Barriers as a Trailblazing Symphony Conductor.”
She has been featured on PBS News Hour Weekend.
Bejarano was also named as One of 10 artists to Watch in KQED Arts’ Bay Brilliant Top 10 Artists of 2018.
She taught herself to play for a year before joining her middle school band.
Bejarano did not discover classical music until her first year in college.
She was also offered a $2000 per year position as assistant conductor of the Peninsula Symphony in Los Altos, California.
